Francesco Risitano (Tau): We pop two words off the stack, and then we use an ALU add, so an algebraic logic unit to do an addition, and then we push the resultant word back onto the stack.

366
00:47:57.940 --> 00:48:05.440
Francesco Risitano (Tau): So it's, you know, the idea is that it should be legible, maintainable, and extensible.

367
00:48:05.740 --> 00:48:11.650
Francesco Risitano (Tau): So, we have 100% compliance with the EAST tests.

368
00:48:11.960 --> 00:48:16.380
Francesco Risitano (Tau): I'm currently doing a bit of a refactor to,

369
00:48:16.690 --> 00:48:22.990
Francesco Risitano (Tau): To align the kind of state model more closely with execution specs so that if.

370
00:48:23.140 --> 00:48:32.759
